WEBVTT

00:02.085 --> 00:02.169
.

00:02.711 --> 00:04.171
male narrator: Europe.

00:05.172 --> 00:07.799
Birthplace of Western
civilization

00:07.841 --> 00:11.762
and a world of unparalleled
culture and sophistication.

00:11.845 --> 00:13.305
[Beethoven's "Symphony No. 5"]

00:13.347 --> 00:14.806
[glass shatters, music stops]

00:14.848 --> 00:17.267
‐ Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa! Whoa!
‐ All right.

00:17.351 --> 00:19.144
narrator: They're back.

00:19.186 --> 00:20.354
‐ Oh, no! Oh‐‐

00:20.395 --> 00:22.523
[shouting indistinctly]

00:22.564 --> 00:24.316
‐ Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa!

00:24.358 --> 00:26.485
narrator:
Four living legends...

00:26.526 --> 00:28.695
‐ William Shatner.
‐ Hey.

00:28.737 --> 00:30.030
narrator: Saddle up again.

00:30.072 --> 00:31.406
‐ Give my best to my family!

00:31.490 --> 00:33.158
narrator:
For a European adventure

00:33.200 --> 00:35.702
they'll never forget.

00:35.744 --> 00:38.288
‐ Whoo!
‐ Oh, no!

00:38.372 --> 00:41.041
narrator:
Starring TV superstar...

00:41.083 --> 00:42.417
‐ You I can't take anywhere.

00:42.501 --> 00:44.002
narrator:
Henry Winkler...

00:44.044 --> 00:45.546
‐ [melodic mumbling]

00:45.587 --> 00:47.589
narrator: Cultural icon...
‐ Oh, my God.

00:47.673 --> 00:49.216
narrator:
William Shatner.

00:49.258 --> 00:50.592
NFL Hall of Famer...

00:50.676 --> 00:52.511
‐ Anybody here know
how to AI a goat?

00:52.552 --> 00:54.012
narrator:
Terry Bradshaw.

00:54.054 --> 00:55.555
‐ What is wrong with you?

00:55.597 --> 00:57.432
narrator:
Former heavyweight champion...

00:57.516 --> 00:59.559
‐ Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa‐‐
narrator: George Foreman.

00:59.601 --> 01:00.310
‐ Oh.

01:00.978 --> 01:02.396
narrator: And...
‐ Ahh!

01:02.437 --> 01:05.732
narrator:
Jeff Dye as the sidekick.

01:05.774 --> 01:07.442
‐ Ahh!
[Bleep], Jeffrey.

01:07.526 --> 01:09.861
narrator: Tonight...
‐ Yodel‐lay‐hee‐hoo!

01:09.903 --> 01:11.113
narrator: Berlin.

01:11.196 --> 01:13.657
‐ How are we gonna get
in that little car?

01:13.740 --> 01:15.033
‐ All right. Go.

01:15.075 --> 01:16.410
‐ Now I know
how toothpaste feels.

01:16.451 --> 01:17.995
‐ It's illegal.
‐ What is?

01:18.078 --> 01:19.871
‐ Spray‐painting.
‐ What are you doing?

01:19.913 --> 01:21.582
You guys.
‐ Hasselhoff rules.

01:21.623 --> 01:24.126
‐ David Hasselhoff,
come on out!

01:24.209 --> 01:26.628
‐ ♪ I've been looking
for freedom ♪

01:26.712 --> 01:28.547
‐ Are you wearing pants
under that?

01:28.589 --> 01:29.756
‐ Hey, that's not funny.
[laughter]

01:29.798 --> 01:31.592
‐ Sorry.
‐ Uncle George!

01:31.633 --> 01:34.386
‐ Hey!
‐ I'm George's friend.

01:34.428 --> 01:35.804
narrator:
Just when you thought

01:35.887 --> 01:38.390
it was safe to go back
on vacation...

01:38.432 --> 01:40.142
‐ You've lost your
ever‐loving mind.

01:40.225 --> 01:42.060
‐ Yep.
narrator: Better late...

01:42.102 --> 01:43.895
‐ Give me a hug, Al.

01:43.937 --> 01:45.397
narrator: Than never.

01:45.439 --> 01:47.983
‐ Another adventure
in another country.

01:48.066 --> 01:49.401
‐ Whoa!

01:49.443 --> 01:50.944
‐ This place is the best.

01:50.986 --> 01:52.571
‐ I gotta go clean
my britches out.

01:52.612 --> 01:56.408
[Lindsey Buckingham's
"Holiday Road"]

01:56.450 --> 01:58.243
‐ ♪ Twist and shout ♪

01:58.285 --> 01:59.995
♪ Come on and let it out ♪

02:00.078 --> 02:02.539
‐ I'm excited to see Berlin.
‐ What are we doing in Berlin?

02:02.622 --> 02:06.418
‐ One of the reasons
that we are here in Germany

02:06.460 --> 02:11.423
is because my parents escaped
from Nazi Germany in 1939.

02:11.465 --> 02:13.300
‐ But you speak German.
‐ Well, I speak German,

02:13.342 --> 02:15.636
'cause they spoke to me
in German in my house.

02:15.677 --> 02:18.305
[speaking German]

02:18.347 --> 02:19.681
[lively pop music]

02:19.765 --> 02:21.516
‐ So, are we gonna
discover your roots?

02:21.600 --> 02:23.268
‐ Well, I don't know. That
is an interesting question.

02:23.310 --> 02:24.770
‐ How do you say "roots"
in German?

02:24.811 --> 02:26.229
‐ "Roots."
‐ "Oots."

02:26.313 --> 02:28.273
‐ I've never actually
been in Berlin,

02:28.315 --> 02:32.110
so this is really
an adventure of a lifetime.

02:32.152 --> 02:33.362
‐ Time to burn some rubber.

02:33.445 --> 02:36.615
[Nena's "99 Luftballons"]

02:36.657 --> 02:38.450
♪ ♪

02:38.492 --> 02:40.994
‐ That's amazing. Wow.

02:41.036 --> 02:42.496
♪ ♪

02:42.537 --> 02:44.665
‐ There's something for you.
‐ Wow.

02:44.706 --> 02:46.333
♪ ♪

02:46.375 --> 02:48.335
‐ Oh, my God.
‐ Yep.

02:48.377 --> 02:52.255
♪ ♪

02:52.339 --> 02:54.800
‐ Wow!
‐ Going to town.

02:54.841 --> 02:56.385
‐ Hey, we're here.

02:56.468 --> 02:59.346
‐ The Brandenburg Gate
is where major things happened.

02:59.388 --> 03:01.139
‐ Whatever that means.

03:01.181 --> 03:03.809
‐ Here we are
at the Brandenburg Gate.

03:03.850 --> 03:05.477
[upbeat guitar music]

03:05.519 --> 03:06.978
‐ Guys, let's take a picture
right in the middle together.

03:07.020 --> 03:09.481
‐ Yeah, yeah, yeah.
‐ Man. All of this history.

03:09.523 --> 03:11.024
Remember what Kennedy said?

03:11.066 --> 03:12.025
[camera shutter clicks]

03:12.067 --> 03:13.235
‐ What?

03:13.318 --> 03:16.530
‐ Ich bin ein Berliner.

03:16.571 --> 03:20.242
‐ Ich bin ein Berliner.
I am a Berliner.

03:20.325 --> 03:21.493
‐ Oh, really?

03:21.535 --> 03:23.787
‐ That's what he said?
‐ Yeah.

03:27.749 --> 03:30.168
‐ All right. Tell me
all of the things about this.

03:30.210 --> 03:31.670
‐ Armies would march through,

03:31.711 --> 03:34.381
and it became
a symbol of victory,

03:34.423 --> 03:35.841
and the Germans
used it as victory.

03:35.882 --> 03:37.676
The Allies marched back
and forth under it.

03:37.717 --> 03:39.386
‐ Napoléon.
‐ Napoléon.

03:39.428 --> 03:41.388
‐ Wait, so who made it?
‐ Frederick the Second.

03:41.430 --> 03:44.015
‐ What, was it a victory
of Prussia over Prussia?

03:44.057 --> 03:45.392
‐ Prussia was part of Germany.

03:45.434 --> 03:46.685
‐ Part of Germany at the time?
‐ Yeah.

03:46.726 --> 03:49.187
‐ Wait, so it was made
"under Prussia?"

03:49.229 --> 03:50.689
[crickets chirping]

03:50.730 --> 03:52.858
‐ I don't really wanna
be next to this guy.

03:52.899 --> 03:56.194
‐ That statue was taken

03:56.236 --> 03:58.113
by Napoléon back to France.

03:58.196 --> 04:00.115
Then when Napoléon
was defeated,

04:00.198 --> 04:01.867
it was taken back to Germany.

04:01.908 --> 04:04.744
‐ There's old Bill over there.
"Oh, well, everybody,

04:04.786 --> 04:08.790
this was built in, uh, 1675,
and, uh..."

04:08.832 --> 04:10.292
‐ What else do we know
about the gate?

04:10.333 --> 04:11.751
‐ Oh, well, that's about it.

04:11.793 --> 04:14.296
‐ ♪ Don't matter
what they say ♪

04:14.379 --> 04:17.799
♪ 'Cause we be killing it
killing it killing it ♪

04:17.883 --> 04:21.052
♪ All the way ♪

04:21.094 --> 04:22.345
‐ Oh!

04:22.429 --> 04:25.140
♪ ♪

04:25.223 --> 04:28.477
[grunts, chuckles]

04:28.560 --> 04:30.395
‐ What part of town is this?

04:30.437 --> 04:31.521
‐ What hotel are we going to?

04:31.605 --> 04:34.107
‐ Actually, here it is.

04:34.149 --> 04:36.568
‐ What is this place?
‐ Look, they spelled it wrong.

04:36.610 --> 04:37.903
The H is missing.
‐ Hostel.

04:37.944 --> 04:40.405
‐ Yeah, and it's by Communists.
‐ Oh.

04:40.447 --> 04:43.408
[lively techno music]

04:43.450 --> 04:50.457
♪ ♪

04:50.832 --> 04:54.669
‐ What exactly about us
says youth hostel?

04:54.753 --> 04:56.755
‐ Oh, yeah.
‐ [whistles]

04:56.797 --> 04:58.340
‐ Wow.
‐ Are you kidding?

04:58.423 --> 05:00.425
‐ Wow.
‐ Ah...

05:00.467 --> 05:01.885
‐ Where are we, bub?

05:01.968 --> 05:03.470
‐ You mean when are we.

05:03.512 --> 05:04.930
‐ Hello.
‐ Hello.

05:04.971 --> 05:06.139
‐ Look at all this old junk.
‐ I'm Henry.

05:06.181 --> 05:07.182
‐ Hi.
‐ This is George.

05:07.265 --> 05:08.517
‐ Brad Pitt.
‐ Hello.

05:08.600 --> 05:10.477
‐ Jeff.
‐ My name is Daniel. Hello.

05:10.519 --> 05:12.479
‐ Bill is coming behind us.
‐ He's out of breath.

05:12.521 --> 05:15.398
Fat people get out of breath
faster than most people.

05:15.482 --> 05:18.735
‐ We've stepped into
Soviet history here.

05:18.819 --> 05:20.111
Very interesting.

05:20.153 --> 05:21.363
‐ I like the decor.

05:21.446 --> 05:22.614
Y'all put a lot
of thought into this.

05:22.656 --> 05:24.366
‐ Everything is original?
‐ Yes.

05:24.449 --> 05:27.536
This is original
GDR Design hotel.

05:27.619 --> 05:29.788
‐ The German
Democratic Republic.

05:29.830 --> 05:30.997
GDR.

05:31.039 --> 05:33.959
Otherwise East Germany,
Communist.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.294
‐ Why, if we're
successful capitalists,

05:36.336 --> 05:37.796
would we stay in
a Communist hotel?

05:37.838 --> 05:39.339
‐ I thought it'd be fun, man.
‐ Yeah.

05:39.381 --> 05:40.924
‐ I've always heard about
the Communist party.

05:41.007 --> 05:42.801
‐ What?
‐ [chuckles] Communist party.

05:42.843 --> 05:45.720
Oh, you're just dumber than
a box of rocks, aren't you?

05:45.804 --> 05:49.558
‐ Did you grow up in East
Germany or in West Germany?

05:49.641 --> 05:50.559
‐ In East Germany.
‐ You did?

05:50.642 --> 05:51.893
‐ Yeah.
‐ Oh.

05:51.977 --> 05:53.728
‐ When David Hasselhoff
took the Wall down,

05:53.812 --> 05:55.480
did you get to see it?
‐ [laughs]

05:55.522 --> 05:56.815
Yes. [laughs]
‐ Yeah?

05:56.857 --> 05:58.275
‐ ♪ I've been looking
for freedom ♪

05:58.358 --> 05:59.818
‐ You were there.
‐ Oh! [laughs]

05:59.860 --> 06:03.405
‐ ♪ I've been looking
for freedom ♪

06:03.488 --> 06:06.157
♪ Since I left my hometown ♪

06:06.199 --> 06:07.492
[cash register dings]

06:07.534 --> 06:08.827
‐ A lot of people
don't know this,

06:08.869 --> 06:10.787
but I'm a huge
David Hasselhoff fan.

06:10.871 --> 06:12.539
I like him mostly
'cause he had a robot car,

06:12.581 --> 06:14.124
and I've always wanted
a robot car.

06:14.207 --> 06:15.500
So, sort of jealous.

06:15.584 --> 06:16.877
And I like that
he lived in a time

06:16.918 --> 06:19.671
when everyone had a mustache,
but he held out.

06:19.713 --> 06:21.506
‐ You know, the Wall
is 96 miles long.

06:21.548 --> 06:23.008
Why didn't he just go
to the end of the wall

06:23.049 --> 06:25.176
and go around the side
and go on the other side?

06:25.218 --> 06:27.178
‐ Uh, what?
‐ [mumbles]

06:27.220 --> 06:28.179
Huh?

06:28.221 --> 06:29.681
[laughter]

06:29.723 --> 06:32.851
[light, playful music]

06:32.893 --> 06:38.690
♪ ♪

06:38.732 --> 06:40.358
‐ So, we need five‐‐five rooms.

06:40.400 --> 06:42.694
‐ [inhales sharply] Now?
‐ Yeah.

06:42.736 --> 06:44.571
‐ We don't have.
‐ You only have four rooms?

06:44.613 --> 06:46.364
‐ Yes.
‐ So, that means two of us

06:46.406 --> 06:48.366
have to stay together.
‐ Oh, boy.

06:53.413 --> 06:54.706
‐ And no elevator.

06:54.789 --> 06:56.916
‐ What?
Do we have air conditioning?

06:56.958 --> 06:58.835
‐ No air conditioning.
‐ What?

06:58.918 --> 07:01.212
‐ Cable television?
‐ Oh, no.

07:01.254 --> 07:02.714
We have a nice garden.
‐ Garden?

07:02.756 --> 07:04.215
‐ You have a gym?
‐ [laughs] No.

07:04.257 --> 07:05.967
‐ You have a phone?
‐ Yeah, this is the phone.

07:06.051 --> 07:09.554
‐ One phone?
‐ Yes, when you talk to Moscow.

07:09.596 --> 07:10.722
‐ All right.

07:10.764 --> 07:12.140
To the rooms, boys.
Here we go.

07:12.223 --> 07:15.060
‐ This is it.
This is the only one left.

07:15.101 --> 07:17.604
Okay. Okay.

07:17.646 --> 07:20.148
Okay, I'm gonna sleep with my
clothes on, if you don't mind.

07:20.231 --> 07:21.566
‐ I don't mind.
‐ No.

07:21.608 --> 07:23.568
‐ That actually is preferable.
‐ Yeah.

07:23.610 --> 07:26.237
I'm sharing a bed with Jeff.

07:26.279 --> 07:28.573
[soft, bright music]

07:28.615 --> 07:29.574
There are some books here.

07:29.616 --> 07:30.784
‐ Books?
‐ Yeah.

07:30.825 --> 07:33.078
I'll just build
the Berlin Wall.

07:33.119 --> 07:35.622
‐ [chuckles] That's about
all books are useful for.

07:35.664 --> 07:37.123
‐ There you go.

07:37.165 --> 07:39.417
‐ Now I'm proud to be able
to tell all of my friends

07:39.459 --> 07:41.586
and family
that I slept with The Fonz.

07:41.628 --> 07:42.754
‐ Hey, you wanna
go out and explore?

07:42.796 --> 07:43.713
‐ Yes.

07:44.631 --> 07:45.590
‐ Should we get the other guys?
‐ Yeah.

07:45.632 --> 07:47.509
Well, it's time to get out
and see Berlin.

07:47.592 --> 07:49.594
‐ All right.
‐ Not only did I get us booked

07:49.636 --> 07:52.305
at a Communist‐themed hostel...

07:52.347 --> 07:53.598
This place is great, huh?

07:53.640 --> 07:56.643
But this place comes
with a Trabi car.

07:56.685 --> 07:58.478
Not sure what that is.

07:58.520 --> 08:00.021
‐ That it?
‐ That says Trabi car.

08:00.105 --> 08:02.607
‐ Are you serious?
‐ How great is this?

08:02.649 --> 08:04.609
[groovy instrumental music]

08:04.651 --> 08:06.778
‐ How are we gonna get
in that little car?

08:06.820 --> 08:08.405
‐ Well, you get in the trunk.

08:08.488 --> 08:12.742
♪ ♪

08:12.826 --> 08:15.620
‐ This could be
the worst car ever made.

08:15.662 --> 08:17.247
Terry, you gotta get in back.

08:17.330 --> 08:19.749
‐ In the back? I got long legs,
you short thing.

08:19.833 --> 08:21.459
‐ Let's do it.
‐ Put me in the trunk.

08:21.501 --> 08:23.461
‐ It's like a clown car.

08:23.503 --> 08:24.629
I'm gonna sit in the middle.

08:24.671 --> 08:26.047
‐ Where'd you get this
piece of junk?

08:26.131 --> 08:27.549
‐ Come on, Georgie.
Don't worry about me.

08:27.632 --> 08:28.800
‐ Big George is in.
‐ Oh, my God.

08:28.842 --> 08:30.844
Now I know
how toothpaste feels.

08:30.885 --> 08:33.179
‐ Oh, my God. I can't breathe.

08:33.221 --> 08:34.389
‐ Okay.
‐ All right.

08:34.472 --> 08:35.473
Go!

08:35.515 --> 08:36.975
[engine grinds]
Ah, dang.

08:37.016 --> 08:38.977
‐ Put it in neutral.
‐ Well, I don't have‐‐

08:39.018 --> 08:41.980
‐ Don't press back.
‐ Oh, my God.

08:42.021 --> 08:44.357
‐ I got a leg cramp, guys.
‐ Come on.

08:44.399 --> 08:45.650
‐ Come on.
[engine ignites, revs]

08:45.692 --> 08:47.277
‐ All right.
‐ That a boy.

08:47.360 --> 08:50.405
Give her some gas.

08:50.488 --> 08:53.158
Oh, no!
‐ No!

08:53.199 --> 08:54.701
[cover of Johnny Cash's
"I've Been Everywhere"]

08:54.743 --> 08:56.494
‐ Who wants to wear
the bear costume?

08:56.536 --> 08:57.996
‐ Not it.
‐ Not it.

08:58.038 --> 09:00.915
‐ Look at how happy he is.
He's never been happier.

09:00.957 --> 09:02.709
‐ There is a glare coming

09:02.751 --> 09:05.003
from between your legs
that is blinding me.

09:05.045 --> 09:06.212
‐ [cackles]

09:06.254 --> 09:08.089
♪ ♪

09:08.173 --> 09:10.675
‐ I'm not attractive.
I need a nose job.

09:10.717 --> 09:12.177
‐ It's cute and it's pert.

09:12.218 --> 09:13.678
‐ You think it's really cute?
‐ It really is.

09:13.720 --> 09:15.305
[bird screeches]

09:21.061 --> 09:21.144
.

09:23.563 --> 09:24.898
[foghorn blares]

09:25.482 --> 09:27.400
‐ This is great.
‐ Oh, no.

09:27.442 --> 09:29.444
‐ We're off to the Wall.

09:29.527 --> 09:31.071
all: Hey!

09:31.112 --> 09:34.074
‐ We're gonna get arrested.
‐ I hope so.

09:34.115 --> 09:35.575
It's the only way
we're gonna live.

09:35.617 --> 09:37.243
‐ Oh, my God.

09:37.285 --> 09:40.288
[rock music]

09:40.330 --> 09:43.875
♪ ♪

09:43.958 --> 09:45.585
‐ Where are we going?
‐ How far is the Wall?

09:45.627 --> 09:47.587
‐ The Wall?
‐ Oh, there it is.

09:47.629 --> 09:54.886
♪ ♪

09:56.763 --> 09:59.641
[people yelling in German]

09:59.724 --> 10:01.643
[cash register dinging]

10:01.726 --> 10:03.061
I think I'm shorter.
‐ Get out.

10:03.103 --> 10:05.230
‐ [speaks German]
‐ My bad.

10:05.271 --> 10:06.898
It was the emergency brake.
Everyone okay?

10:06.940 --> 10:08.900
‐ That was some stop.
‐ There we go, yeah.

10:08.942 --> 10:10.151
I wanted to be close
with these guys,

10:10.235 --> 10:11.903
but I didn't want
to be this close.

10:11.945 --> 10:13.571
‐ [grunting loudly]

10:13.613 --> 10:15.949
‐ I am never...

10:15.990 --> 10:18.451
going back in this car again.

10:18.493 --> 10:19.786
‐ How are you gonna get home?

10:19.828 --> 10:22.330
‐ Like a clown car.

10:22.372 --> 10:25.834
‐ In Berlin, there's graffiti
everywhere.

10:25.875 --> 10:28.002
It is 100% illegal

10:28.086 --> 10:30.588
to spray paint
the Berlin Wall,

10:30.630 --> 10:33.800
but a bunch of
other people did it.

10:33.842 --> 10:36.803
[slow electronic music]

10:36.845 --> 10:39.806
♪ ♪

10:39.848 --> 10:41.808
‐ Oh, no, I‐‐

10:41.850 --> 10:43.393
‐ It's illegal.
‐ What is?

10:43.476 --> 10:44.686
‐ Spray painting.

10:44.769 --> 10:45.979
‐ Everyone else is doing it.
Look.

10:46.020 --> 10:47.188
‐ You can't do it.
‐ I'll do it.

10:47.272 --> 10:49.107
How do I do it?
‐ It's illegal.

10:49.149 --> 10:51.025
Don't spray that.
Don't do that.

10:51.109 --> 10:52.986
‐ I'm not sure about this.

10:53.027 --> 10:56.990
It's an historic
and important landmark.

10:57.031 --> 11:00.702
I haven't broken a law
like this maybe in my life.

11:00.785 --> 11:01.870
‐ Look what Terry's doing.

11:01.953 --> 11:04.205
[spray can hissing]

11:04.247 --> 11:06.040
‐ [cackles]
‐ What are you doing?

11:06.082 --> 11:07.709
You guys.
‐ Ha!

11:07.750 --> 11:10.962
‐ This is "go to jail"
illegal.

11:11.004 --> 11:14.340
It is not just highly illegal,
you could be arrested.

11:14.382 --> 11:16.134
We're observing
you break the law.

11:16.176 --> 11:17.677
‐ What did you write?
‐ "Bradshaw 12."

11:17.719 --> 11:19.679
‐ "Stud."
‐ Okay.

11:19.721 --> 11:21.973
‐ Terry.
‐ So, Terry's on the Wall.

11:22.015 --> 11:24.559
‐ I'm on the Wall forever.
‐ Watch this.

11:24.642 --> 11:27.145
[groovy instrumental music]

11:27.187 --> 11:28.646
‐ Oh, no.

11:28.688 --> 11:30.815
‐ Oh...
‐ Shatner.

11:30.857 --> 11:32.358
That is just‐‐

11:32.400 --> 11:35.737
‐ Why would you write
over Terry's name?

