15:58.499 --> 16:00.835
[seat whirs]
‐ [laughs]

16:00.918 --> 16:02.461
[baby giggling]

16:02.503 --> 16:03.880
‐ Oh, man.

16:03.963 --> 16:06.007
Ooh, what the?

16:06.090 --> 16:08.342
Uh‐oh.
‐ Bye, George.

16:08.426 --> 16:10.803
‐ What's going on here?
Whoa...

16:10.845 --> 16:14.140
‐ Guys, let's go somewhere
where it's safer to sit.

16:14.182 --> 16:15.641
‐ Yeah.
‐ I'm all for that.

16:15.683 --> 16:17.602
‐ Let's go over here.
‐ Dinner's on me, guys.

16:17.643 --> 16:21.314
I'm flush with cash.
[cackles]

16:21.355 --> 16:23.816
‐ What else? What does
anybody else want to see here?

16:23.858 --> 16:25.151
‐ I don't know
nothing about Berlin.

16:25.193 --> 16:27.528
‐ Well, Berlin is a very
sophisticated city.

16:27.612 --> 16:29.280
‐ You say that
about every city.

16:29.322 --> 16:31.115
‐ No, but this is a‐‐
‐ Whoa.

16:31.157 --> 16:34.619
[mechanical whirring]

16:34.660 --> 16:36.287
‐ This place is the best.
‐ Finding your roots

16:36.329 --> 16:37.830
is the most important
thing for you.

16:37.872 --> 16:40.249
‐ Right. That's right.
Finding my‐‐oh!

16:40.333 --> 16:42.168
[rumbling]
‐ God dang. [bleep].

16:42.210 --> 16:44.170
‐ Hello. Oh, hello.
‐ Finding your senses.

16:44.212 --> 16:45.546
‐ That startled me.

16:45.630 --> 16:48.299
‐ Henry, are we really gonna
see some evidence

16:48.341 --> 16:50.134
that your family were here?

16:50.176 --> 16:51.677
‐ It would be amazing.

16:51.719 --> 16:54.847
My mother, my mother's
parents lived here.

16:54.889 --> 16:56.015
‐ Wouldn't that be something

16:56.057 --> 16:57.183
if we could see
where they're...

16:57.225 --> 16:58.684
It would mean so much for me

16:58.726 --> 17:02.313
to see Henry's family,
where they started.

17:02.355 --> 17:05.733
‐ I have all these pictures
of my grandparents,

17:05.816 --> 17:08.819
of my great grandparents,
aunts and uncles,

17:08.861 --> 17:10.529
my parents.

17:10.571 --> 17:13.741
So, the story was that
my father was able to get

17:13.824 --> 17:17.662
a six‐week work visa
to come to New York City,

17:17.703 --> 17:21.999
but Uncle Helmut was having
a white dinner jacket made

17:22.083 --> 17:24.543
and it was going to be
ready the next day.

17:24.585 --> 17:27.213
So, instead of going
with my dad

17:27.255 --> 17:30.841
and my mom and leaving Berlin,

17:30.883 --> 17:32.677
he stayed an extra day,

17:32.718 --> 17:36.514
and that night
was taken by the Nazis.

17:36.556 --> 17:41.394
I would love to just see
the street somebody walked down

17:41.435 --> 17:44.522
and that I can walk down.
‐ Yeah.

17:44.564 --> 17:46.524
This is a great city
for Henry to visit,

17:46.566 --> 17:50.361
because this is where
his roots started from.

17:50.403 --> 17:53.197
This is where it
all began for him,

17:53.239 --> 17:54.365
the story of his family.

17:54.407 --> 17:55.783
That's why this trip
is important.

17:55.866 --> 17:57.201
‐ Right.

17:57.243 --> 17:59.370
‐ Another adventure
in another country.

17:59.412 --> 18:00.913
‐ Ah!
‐ I love you guys.

18:00.997 --> 18:02.707
Oh, my God.

18:02.790 --> 18:03.958
Ah, now it's dusty.

18:04.000 --> 18:05.418
‐ I'm not doing this.

18:05.459 --> 18:07.712
‐ It got dust in my brew.
‐ I can't drink it now.

18:07.753 --> 18:10.214
‐ I gotta go clean
my britches out.

18:10.256 --> 18:11.882
[bird screeches]

18:17.096 --> 18:17.138
.

18:19.056 --> 18:22.101
[patriotic music]

18:22.768 --> 18:23.936
‐ The Waltz is huge in Germany.

